# Compliance Officer / Senior Compliance Office
You will report to the Chief Compliance Officer, and you will be responsible for building out a compliance program of a financial institution. You will conduct periodical compliance reviews, reports, a compliance monitoring program and ensure regulatory oversight of a financial institution on a day-to-day basis.
## Responsibilities and skills:
- Contributing to the ongoing compliance monitoring plan, policies, procedures, processes;
- Contributing to the daily compliance tasks;
- Overseeing a variety of compliance projects, including thematic reviews;
- Developing the existing compliance manuals and documentation;
- Demonstrating critical thinking and the ability to bring order to unstructured problems;
- Using a broad range of tools and techniques to extract insights from sector trends;
- Knowing how and when to use tools available for a given situation and being able to explain the reasons for your choice;
- Communicating with others in a straightforward and structured way.

## Qualifications and requirements
A successful candidate has a bachelor’s degree or higher, and at least four years of relevant experience. Proven experience in FSI, credit institution or FinTech is desired. Additional personal/ industry qualifications would be an advantage.

**Salary:** 4,500-6,000 euro (brutto)

Please submit your application by email: [cv@travelunion.eu](mailto:cv@travelunion.eu)

By sending your CV, you agree to UAB "Travel Union" [Candidate Policy Notice](https://mytu.lt/teisine-informacija?document=CP).

# Content Creator
Travel Union is a fast-growing mobile banking solutions provider licensed by the Bank of Lithuania. myTU, the primary product of Travel Union aims to economise mobile banking by offering free account creation, payment card, and daily banking services. We utilise proprietary core banking technology to provide a superior experience for tens of thousands of customers who have trusted our app for their daily banking needs. Our mobile banking app is available throughout the European Union and it’s rated 4,4/5 on the Play Store & App Store. 

Video has changed the way we consume content in the past few years. We are passionate about educating, entertaining, and inspiring our existing and potential customer base to benefit from secure mobile banking. Our product is loved by frequent travellers for the ease of using myTU payment card overseas, parents who streamline finances for their children, freelancers who can earn in euros, and others wanting an intuitive app for their daily banking needs. Banking is not very exciting, but we aim to add a fun twist to it. 

We are looking for a talented Content Creator who can showcase our product uniquely in the banking space as an ideal solution for travel, for families, and freelancers. If you are someone who is a natural at creating content, loves travelling and wants freedom to be creative in your work, write to us at cv@travelunion.eu. 

## Required knowledge and skills
- At least 2+ years of experience creating engaging and inspiring video content for social media (TikTok, Instagram, YouTube)
- Knowledge of social media trends and creativity in this field;
- Ability to turn ideas into content; 
- Bringing great new ideas about advertising to the table;
- Excellent proficiency in English;
- An understanding of SEO best practices is a plus;
- Examples of your previous work.

## What you will be doing
- Shooting and editing various videos for our brand;
- Creating native content for social media platforms (including TikTok, Instagram and Youtube);
- Brainstorming and suggesting new ways to promote company offerings and to reach new consumers;
- Writing, reviewing, editing, and updating content for the company websites, blogs, marketing materials, and similar platforms;
- Assisting the creative team with the design of promotional materials;
- Suggesting ideas for campaigns with primary research and visualising them for the comprehension of the wider team;

## Benefits
- Motivating salary;  
- Flexible working hours; 
- Possibility to work remotely, in the office or a mix of both :) 
- Opportunity to grow with an innovative FinTech start-up   
- A professional, motivating and friendly team; 
- What else would you like? Let us know and we’ll try to arrange it!  

**Salary:** 1,200 - 2,000 euro (brutto)

Please submit your application by email: [cv@travelunion.eu](mailto:cv@travelunion.eu)

By sending your CV, you agree to UAB "Travel Union" [Candidate Policy Notice](https://mytu.lt/teisine-informacija?document=CP).
